  <article class="article-body">

    <p>devopsellence is VM-native deployment tooling. You run <code>devopsellence deploy</code> and your Dockerized app is live with managed HTTPS, zero-downtime rollouts, and secret injection &mdash; on servers you own. No Kubernetes. No Helm. No shared multi-tenant infrastructure.</p>

    <p>Most tools that offer this experience store everything in one place: secrets in the database, deploy state behind the API, images in a self-hosted registry. The coordination layer becomes a single point of failure for both management and runtime. If it goes down, everything goes down.</p>

    <p>We chose a different path.</p>

    <h2>The three-layer split</h2>

    <p>devopsellence separates deployment coordination from application delivery and execution:</p>

    <div class="article-diagram">
      <div class="article-diagram-row">
        <div class="article-diagram-box article-diagram-box--blue">
          <strong>Control plane</strong>
          <span>Coordinates deploys, manages identity, publishes signed state. Never touches your traffic or secrets at runtime.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
